00:03:14.960 --> 00:03:19.240
In this shape, the ciliary muscle in the ciliary body is thin and not contracted.

00:03:19.540 --> 00:03:23.260
I see! The lens is pulled flat by the zonules, 

00:03:23.700 --> 00:03:29.120
so the muscles in the ciliary body are relaxed, which causes tension on the zonules.  

00:03:29.400 --> 00:03:31.060
That’s clear! Now, for looking at something that’s close

